HEADWORD: Crotchetiness
<hw>Crotch"et*i*ness</hw> <pr>(kr?ch"?t-?-n?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The state or character of being crotchety, or whimsical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This belief in rightness is a kind of conscientiousness, and when
it degenerates it becomes <qex>crotchetiness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Grote.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crotchety</ent>⟦br⟧
